PPMS Oracle Cloud Free Tier VM Setup
====================================

Target path on VM:
/home/ubuntu/ppms

Expected structure:
/home/ubuntu/ppms/
├── docker-compose.yml
├── .env
├── backend.Dockerfile
├── nginx/
│   └── nginx.conf
├── scripts/
│   ├── backup.sh
│   └── duckdns.sh
├── backups/
├── logs/
│   ├── backend/
│   └── nginx/
├── ppms-backend/
└── ppms-frontend/

1. Install Docker + Docker Compose
----------------------------------
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg cron snapd
sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
sudo curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc
sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc
echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(. /etc/os-release && echo "$VERSION_CODENAME") stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin
sudo systemctl enable --now docker
sudo systemctl enable --now cron

2. Install Certbot
------------------
sudo snap install core
sudo snap refresh core
sudo snap install --classic certbot
sudo ln -sf /snap/bin/certbot /usr/bin/certbot

3. Create folders
-----------------
sudo mkdir -p /home/ubuntu/ppms
sudo mkdir -p /home/ubuntu/postgres-data
sudo mkdir -p /home/ubuntu/backups
sudo mkdir -p /home/ubuntu/ppms/backups
sudo mkdir -p /home/ubuntu/ppms/logs/backend
sudo mkdir -p /home/ubuntu/ppms/logs/nginx
sudo chown -R ubuntu:ubuntu /home/ubuntu/ppms /home/ubuntu/postgres-data /home/ubuntu/backups

4. Copy project and infra files
-------------------------------
cp -r ppms/* /home/ubuntu/ppms/
cp -r ppms-backend /home/ubuntu/ppms/
cp -r ppms-frontend /home/ubuntu/ppms/
chmod +x /home/ubuntu/ppms/scripts/backup.sh
chmod +x /home/ubuntu/ppms/scripts/duckdns.sh

5. Edit environment file
------------------------
nano /home/ubuntu/ppms/.env

Minimum values:
POSTGRES_DB=ppms
POSTGRES_USER=ppms_user
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=strong-password
DOMAIN_NAME=your-subdomain.duckdns.org
CERTBOT_EMAIL=you@example.com
DUCKDNS_DOMAIN=your-subdomain
DUCKDNS_TOKEN=your-duckdns-token
BACKUP_DIR=/home/ubuntu/backups

6. Create DuckDNS subdomain
---------------------------
Open:
https://www.duckdns.org

Then create your subdomain and put the token into /home/ubuntu/ppms/.env

7. Update DuckDNS and verify DNS
--------------------------------
cd /home/ubuntu/ppms
./scripts/duckdns.sh
getent hosts your-subdomain.duckdns.org

8. Build frontend
-----------------
sudo docker run --rm -v /home/ubuntu/ppms/ppms-frontend:/workspace -w /workspace node:22-alpine sh -lc "npm ci && npm run build"

9. Build backend jar
--------------------
sudo docker run --rm -v /home/ubuntu/ppms/ppms-backend:/workspace -w /workspace maven:3.9.11-eclipse-temurin-21 mvn clean package -DskipTests

10. Start postgres and backend
------------------------------
cd /home/ubuntu/ppms
sudo docker compose up -d postgres backend

11. Generate SSL certificate
----------------------------
sudo certbot certonly --standalone -d your-subdomain.duckdns.org --agree-tos -m you@example.com --non-interactive

12. Start nginx
---------------
cd /home/ubuntu/ppms
sudo docker compose up -d nginx

13. Verify HTTPS
----------------
sudo docker compose ps
curl -I https://your-subdomain.duckdns.org
curl -I http://your-subdomain.duckdns.org

Cron jobs
---------
( sudo crontab -l 2>/dev/null; \
  echo "0 2 * * * /home/ubuntu/ppms/scripts/backup.sh >> /home/ubuntu/ppms/logs/backup-cron.log 2>&1"; \
  echo "*/5 * * * * /home/ubuntu/ppms/scripts/duckdns.sh >> /home/ubuntu/ppms/logs/duckdns-cron.log 2>&1"; \
  echo "15 4 * * * certbot renew --quiet && docker restart ppms-nginx >> /home/ubuntu/ppms/logs/certbot-renew.log 2>&1" \
) | sudo crontab -

Troubleshooting
---------------
cd /home/ubuntu/ppms
sudo docker compose logs -f postgres
sudo docker compose logs -f backend
sudo docker compose logs -f nginx
sudo docker compose ps
sudo docker exec -it ppms-postgres pg_isready -U ppms_user -d ppms
sudo docker exec -it ppms-backend curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:8080/actuator/health

Reminder
--------
Open Oracle Cloud ingress/security rules for TCP ports 80 and 443.
